I stopped by today after work to order a medium chicken poppers with Cajun fries. While the chicken poppers were alright, the fries were unfortunately dreadful. They had a terrible aftertaste which I believe might have been due to the oil used to fry them. Although that’s just speculation, the disgusting aftertaste they left in my mouth is a fact. It was so bad I couldn’t force myself to finish the meal even after drenching the fries in both sauces (Thai Sweet Chilli and Chipotle Aioli) and several packets of ketchup. I ended up having to throw the entire box of food out and literally wasted my money.  P.S. I went there quite late, about 11:15pm and they close at 12am. If the oil was the reason for the taste of the fries then I’m speculating (again) it’s because it was late however, I expected a decent meal and paid for such so the disappointment still stands.
